1. Overview

This proposal outlines a three-phase approach to modernize data visualization and reporting for the EPB system.
The solution balances speed, flexibility, and scalability by combining a nightly ETL pipeline, the open-source Metabase BI platform, and a custom interactive dashboard layer.

‚∏ª

	‚Ä¢	Establish a centralized analytics data store decoupled from the ERP production database.

	‚Ä¢	Develop custom interactive dashboards for long-term, real-time, and business-specific visualization needs.

‚∏ª

3. Proposed Architecture

Phase 1 ‚Äî ETL Data Pipeline

Goal: Create a nightly data synchronization from the EPB on-premise database into an analytics database (PostgreSQL recommended).

Key points:
	‚Ä¢	Extract data from EPB DB (e.g., sales, inventory, customer).
	‚Ä¢	Transform into clean, analytics-friendly schemas.
	‚Ä¢	Load into PostgreSQL tables optimized for reporting (summary, trend, aggregate).
	‚Ä¢	Schedule nightly ETL jobs via Laravel Scheduler, Airflow, or cron.

	‚Ä¢	Offloads heavy read operations from ERP DB.
	‚Ä¢	Maintains historical consistency for trend analysis.
	‚Ä¢	Enables faster analytical queries.

Goal: Embed validated Metabase charts into a custom-built dashboard (Laravel + React/Vue) and extend with custom visualizations.
